	<meta property="og:description" content="By Eddie Waldo from wsj.com, Sep 9 ValueAct Capital Management LP has reached a deal to buy a 4% stake in Seagate, a transaction the company itself arranged after a big shareholder said it planned to sell. The deal is yet another sign that some activist investors are taking a gentler approach with companies, helping [&hellip;]" />
