        <main class="site-main" role="main">
            
	<article class="news" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/NewsArticle">

		<section class="banner banner--xs">
			<div class="container container--md">
				<h1 class="banner__headline" itemprop="headline">Activist on Call: Seagate Brokers Deal to Bring in ValueAct Capital</h1>
				<time class="banner__time" itemprop="datePublished" content="2016-09-09">09 September, 2016</time>
			</div>
		</section>
		<section class="content pad--t0">
			<div class="container container--md">
				<img class="aligncenter" src="https://valueact.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/news-seagate-800x450-c-center.jpg" alt="Activist on Call: Seagate Brokers Deal to Bring in ValueAct Capital" itemprop="image" />
				<h5>By Eddie Waldo from wsj.com, Sep 9</h5>
<p>ValueAct Capital Management LP has reached a deal to buy a 4% stake in Seagate, a transaction the company itself arranged after a big shareholder said it planned to sell.</p>
<p>The deal is yet another sign that some activist investors are taking a gentler approach with companies, helping them through transitions rather than pushing for dramatic changes &#8230;</p>
<div class="clearfix"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/valueact-capital-takes-larger-stake-in-seagate-1473435294?mod=rss_Technology"> Full article here.</a></div>
<div class="clearfix"></div>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: left;"><sub><small>Disclaimer: The current and former portfolio companies shown on this page reflect those investments made by ValueAct Capital since ValueAct Capital’s inception: (i) that were or are a publicly disclosed position in a Schedule 13D; or (ii) were disclosed in an investor quarterly letter, which is generally determined by the chief investment officer based on subjective factors such as length of expected holding period, level of due diligence on the portfolio company, and relative size of the investment. The companies shown on this page do not represent all of the investments purchased or sold by funds managed by ValueAct Capital. It should not be assumed that any or all of these investments were or will be profitable. While ValueAct Capital expects to maintain concentrated portfolios and take an active role with respect to its investments, ValueAct Capital expects to own, and in the past has owned, a number of other investments without taking an active role with respect to such investments.<br />
</small></sub></p>

			</div>
		</section>

	</article>


